<p>I'm currently using the following to create relative URL's on my site: </p>  <p>Above my <code>&lt;!DOCTYPE&gt;</code>:</p>  <pre><code>$domain = "http://" . $_SERVER['HTTP_HOST']; </code></pre>  <p>Then, my URL's:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;a href="&lt;?php echo $domain; ?&gt;/page/"&gt;Example&lt;/a&gt; </code></pre>  <p>My questions are A) is this the most effective way of doing this? And B) how would I use something like this when working with a simple include? </p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php include ("./include/header.php"); ?&gt; </code></pre>  <ul> <li>Are you using a framework? No</li> <li>Are you building a complex system? No</li> <li>Are you calling or implementing an API? No </li> <li>Will your code be reused? Yes, but with very simple websites.</li> <li>It has dependencies? Will it have? No</li> </ul>